title: Python
content: Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language. It emphasizes code readability with its notable use of significant whitespace.

title: NumPy
content: NumPy is the fundamental package for numerical computing with Python. It provides support for arrays and matrices, along with a collection of mathematical functions. ![NumPy Logo](https://numpy.org/images/logo.svg)

title: Pandas
content: Pandas is a powerful data manipulation and analysis library. It provides data structures like DataFrames that simplify working with structured data. ![Pandas Logo](https://pandas.pydata.org/static/img/pandas_white.svg)

title: Matplotlib
content: Matplotlib is a plotting library that creates static, animated, and interactive visualizations in Python. ![Matplotlib Plot](https://matplotlib.org/_static/logo2_compressed.svg)

title: Scikit-learn
content: Scikit-learn is a simple and efficient library for machine learning, offering tools for classification, regression, clustering, and dimensionality reduction. ![Scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/_static/scikit-learn-logo-small.png)

title: Flask
content: Flask is a lightweight WSGI web application framework in Python. It is designed to make getting started quick and easy, with the ability to scale up to complex applications. ![Flask Logo](https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.2.x/_images/flask-logo.png)

title: TensorFlow
content: TensorFlow is a comprehensive open-source platform for machine learning developed by Google. It offers tools for building and deploying ML models. ![TensorFlow](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2d/Tensorflow_logo.svg)

title: PyTorch
content: PyTorch is an open-source deep learning platform developed by Facebook's AI Research lab. It is known for its flexibility and ease of use in research. ![PyTorch](https://pytorch.org/assets/images/pytorch-logo.png)

title: OpenCV
content: OpenCV (Open Source Computer Vision Library) is an open-source computer vision and machine learning software library. It has over 2500 optimized algorithms. ![OpenCV](https://opencv.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/OpenCV_logo_black-2.png)

title: Seaborn
content: Seaborn is a data visualization library based on matplotlib. It provides a high-level interface for drawing attractive and informative statistical graphics. ![Seaborn](https://seaborn.pydata.org/_static/logo-wide-lightbg.svg)

title: Plotly
content: Plotly is an interactive graphing library that enables the creation of web-based visualizations like line charts, bar graphs, and 3D plots. ![Plotly](https://images.plot.ly/logo/new-branding/plotly-logomark.png)

title: BeautifulSoup
content: BeautifulSoup is a Python library used for pulling data out of HTML and XML files. It creates parse trees from page source code. ![BeautifulSoup](https://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/bs4/doc/_images/6.1.jpg)

title: Requests
content: Requests is a simple HTTP library for Python, built for human beings. It allows sending HTTP requests easily. ![Requests](https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/latest/_static/requests-sidebar.png)

title: Tkinter
content: Tkinter is the standard GUI library for Python. It provides tools to create graphical user interfaces. ![Tkinter](https://files.realpython.com/media/Tkinter_Walkthrough_Watermarked.71558ae6bf94.jpg)

title: Django
content: Django is a high-level Python web framework that encourages rapid development and clean, pragmatic design. ![Django](https://static.djangoproject.com/img/logos/django-logo-negative.png)

title: FastAPI
content: FastAPI is a modern, fast web framework for building APIs with Python 3.7+ based on standard Python type hints. ![FastAPI](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/img/logo-margin/logo-teal.png)
